<body>
  <h1>Experiment Overview</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Project Summary</h2>
    <p>
      PROJECT FORGET ME is a classified psychological experiment focused on memory manipulation and control of human subjects. Subjects are monitored continuously in a controlled environment, and their cognitive responses to various stimuli are recorded for analysis.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Investigate methods to induce selective amnesia.</li>
      <li>Explore behavioral conditioning through memory loops.</li>
      <li>Assess emotional responses under controlled stress.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Subjects are isolated in simulated environments with intermittent exposure to memory triggers. Data is collected through digital diaries, biometric sensors, and observational logs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Safety Protocols</h2>
    <p>
      All procedures comply with internal ethical standards. Sedation and monitoring protocols are strictly enforced to prevent harm.
    </p>
  </section>

